  <!-- ===================================================================
       ROW 6 — Quick start
       =================================================================== -->
  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>QUICK START</title>
      <description>Get SENTINEL running end-to-end in a Splunk Enterprise instance.</description>
      <html>
        <ol style="font-size:0.85rem; color:#E8ECF4; line-height:1.9; padding-left:1.25rem;">
          <li>Install the SENTINEL app under <code style="color:#A8D8A8;">$SPLUNK_HOME/etc/apps/sentinel</code> and restart Splunk.</li>
          <li>Configure credentials and MCP/SAIA endpoints in <code style="color:#A8D8A8;">local/sentinel.conf</code>.</li>
          <li>Verify indexes <code style="color:#A8D8A8;">sentinel_cases</code>, <code style="color:#A8D8A8;">sentinel_audit</code>, and <code style="color:#A8D8A8;">sentinel_metrics</code> are created (see <code style="color:#A8D8A8;">indexes.conf</code>).</li>
          <li>Enable the orchestrator input in <code style="color:#A8D8A8;">inputs.conf</code> to start the agent pipeline.</li>
          <li>Open the <strong>War Room</strong> dashboard to monitor live cases, agent health, and pending approvals.</li>
          <li>Review the Approval Gate queue regularly — eradication-tier actions require human sign-off within 5 minutes.</li>
        </ol>
      </html>
    </panel>
  </row>

